        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> An interesting idea - for fun rather than any kind of elitism - but there's a slight bump.</P><P>Let's say I wanted to set up a private necromancer forum over at the NecroGnomicon, in addition to the public forums.  Invitation only, password protected, and invisible if you're not on the guest list.  Interested necromancers could set up an EZ Board account and post their server on a public forum; they'd be put on the guest list and given the password in-game when their "necromancy" is verified.</P><P>The problem is, how would you go about inviting people to it?  If you just go trolling around servers sending tells to high-level necros you'd just get a lot of "not interested" responses, and the word would get out quick.  If you didn't let people know it's there, how would you know who's interested so you could get on with inviting them?</P><P>Also, there'd be no way to guarantee that VI folk can't get in.  All it would take is a verifiable high-level necromancer and a non-work e-mail address.  I don't personally see that as a problem, but there it is.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247832" target="_blank">Morty Undercrypt</a>, Keeper of the <a href="http://www.necrognomicon.com/" target="_blank">NecroGnomicon</a><BR><font size=1>"I am the truth, and the truth shall make you flee."</font id=size1><BR>E'ci</font></td>
